712
00:40:54,034 --> 00:40:55,953
- Go-eun
- Yeah.

713
00:40:56,579 --> 00:40:57,872
Gosh, you've been busy.

714
00:40:58,706 --> 00:41:00,916
- I haven't been feeling that great.
- What's wrong?

715
00:41:01,876 --> 00:41:03,127
I didn't get much sleep.

716
00:41:03,210 --> 00:41:04,336
- You didn't?
- No.

717
00:41:04,420 --> 00:41:06,380
You must have had fun yesterday.

718
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:07,798
- Yesterday?
- Yeah.

719
00:41:08,841 --> 00:41:09,884
Well, you know.

720
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:11,552
- Hmm?
- Huh?

721
00:41:18,350 --> 00:41:20,769
How was it yesterday?
Did you have a good time?

722
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:24,190
- Inferno was nice.
- Really?

723
00:41:24,273 --> 00:41:26,275
- You know, the weather was cool.
- Yeah?

724
00:41:27,026 --> 00:41:29,778
The view was beautiful,
the food was pretty good.

725
00:41:29,862 --> 00:41:31,238
And I had fun with Ha-eun.

726
00:41:32,114 --> 00:41:35,868
We felt like siblings within five minutes
of meeting each other. I was taken aback.

727
00:41:37,161 --> 00:41:40,289
- Mm.
- So, yeah, there you go.

728
00:41:45,211 --> 00:41:46,504
Mm.

729
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:53,594
So, where are you at, <i>oppa</i>?
I can't figure out your feelings at all.

730
00:41:57,264 --> 00:41:58,724
I, um…

731
00:42:02,937 --> 00:42:06,690
You know, we were just wondering
if the fact we got along so well

732
00:42:06,774 --> 00:42:11,570
and felt comfortable with each other
was because we felt like siblings or not.

733
00:42:11,654 --> 00:42:13,489
Talking to Ha-eun gave me…

734
00:42:14,573 --> 00:42:15,658
a clear idea.

735
00:42:15,741 --> 00:42:16,700
- Mm.
- Yeah.

736
00:42:17,701 --> 00:42:19,495
Of what it is I'm feeling for you.

737
00:42:21,455 --> 00:42:23,999
- Oh.
- Yeah.

738
00:42:24,083 --> 00:42:25,918
And talking to Ha-eun last night…

739
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:28,212
LAST NIGHT

740
00:42:28,295 --> 00:42:30,297
What if tomorrow she suddenly does a 180

741
00:42:30,381 --> 00:42:33,509
and starts pursuing you aggressively?
What would you do then?

742
00:42:33,592 --> 00:42:35,302
A girl I'm attracted to?

743
00:42:36,303 --> 00:42:38,055
Well, then I'd kiss her.

744
00:42:38,138 --> 00:42:39,974
Are you crazy? What's wrong with you?

745
00:42:40,057 --> 00:42:42,309
You're so annoying. You make my head hurt.

746
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:45,271
It made me think she's like a sibling.

747
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:50,317
And it made me realize that
what I feel for you is romantic.

748
00:42:51,652 --> 00:42:53,153
I'm sure of that now.

749
00:42:54,863 --> 00:42:56,657
So that's how you feel then, <i>oppa.</i>

750
00:42:57,783 --> 00:43:00,160
How could you have been
completely oblivious to that?

751
00:43:00,244 --> 00:43:02,288
- Well…
- Yeah, that's so crazy.

752
00:43:02,371 --> 00:43:04,248
Or is it because I never told you?

753
00:43:05,499 --> 00:43:06,542
Didn't I?

754
00:43:07,042 --> 00:43:09,378
Well, even though I never told you…

755
00:43:09,461 --> 00:43:11,171
You thought I'd know anyway?

756
00:43:12,339 --> 00:43:13,966
Yeah, because I just thought that we had

757
00:43:14,049 --> 00:43:16,010
a lot of fun together
when we went to Paradise.

758
00:43:16,093 --> 00:43:18,470
- Yeah, we did.
- I guess I just naturally thought

759
00:43:18,554 --> 00:43:22,099
you would have some idea
even if I didn't spell it out.

760
00:43:22,182 --> 00:43:25,227
- Ah.
- But I've learned something new here,

761
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:26,770
that I need to spell it out.

762
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:30,566
Enough about me, though.
Where are you at now?

763
00:43:34,361 --> 00:43:36,071
Well, right now,

764
00:43:37,323 --> 00:43:41,452
- I'll be honest with you. I like Sung-min.
- Mm.

765
00:43:41,535 --> 00:43:44,288
- What?
- Wait, really?

766
00:43:44,371 --> 00:43:47,374
She actually meant that?
Oh, I'm sorry. I really--

767
00:43:47,458 --> 00:43:50,753
- She's not a person who just says things.
- You're right.

768
00:43:50,836 --> 00:43:52,254
All our predictions were way off.

769
00:43:52,338 --> 00:43:55,007
Go-eun's just a really
honest person, isn't she?

770
00:43:55,090 --> 00:43:57,760
- She just came out and said it.
- She is. You're right.

771
00:43:57,843 --> 00:44:01,096
I'll be honest with you, I like Sung-min.

772
00:44:01,180 --> 00:44:02,222
Mm.

773
00:44:03,682 --> 00:44:06,226
- Have you talked to him?
- Yeah, we've talked a lot.

774
00:44:06,310 --> 00:44:07,394
Mm.

775
00:44:09,104 --> 00:44:10,481
I want to keep talking.

776
00:44:11,148 --> 00:44:12,107
With who?

777
00:44:12,191 --> 00:44:14,026
- You and me.
- Mm.

778
00:44:14,109 --> 00:44:15,361
Let's do that.

779
00:44:17,946 --> 00:44:20,407
What kind of guys
did you say you usually dated?

780
00:44:21,617 --> 00:44:24,203
- Did you say they were all different?
- I… Yeah.

781
00:44:25,037 --> 00:44:26,664
What attracts you?

782
00:44:29,667 --> 00:44:32,086
No, actually, what doesn't attract you?

783
00:44:32,169 --> 00:44:35,130
- What doesn't attract?
- Like, "This really turns me off."

784
00:44:35,214 --> 00:44:36,548
What would that be?

785
00:44:36,632 --> 00:44:37,800
Oh.

786
00:44:37,883 --> 00:44:39,635
Well, I don't like short arms.

787
00:44:47,184 --> 00:44:49,186
- I know exactly what you mean.
- You know, right?

788
00:44:49,269 --> 00:44:51,230
I totally do.
That's something I notice, too.

789
00:44:51,313 --> 00:44:52,147
Yeah.

790
00:44:55,484 --> 00:44:56,443
Anything else?

791
00:44:56,527 --> 00:44:57,361
- More?
- Yeah.

792
00:44:57,444 --> 00:44:59,488
I dislike people who don't apologize.

793
00:44:59,571 --> 00:45:00,948
- Apologize?
- Yeah.

794
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:04,618
I like people who can say
"I'm sorry" and "thank you."

795
00:45:04,702 --> 00:45:06,161
Someone with manners.

796
00:45:06,245 --> 00:45:07,788
Someone who's expressive?

797
00:45:07,871 --> 00:45:09,206
- Yeah.
- Okay.

798
00:45:09,289 --> 00:45:11,542
What about you?
What makes you go "I really hate this"?

799
00:45:11,625 --> 00:45:13,210
- I really hate this?
- Yeah.

800
00:45:14,002 --> 00:45:15,587
Okay. So, you know…

801
00:45:15,671 --> 00:45:17,798
You know how everyone
has their own unique scent?

802
00:45:17,881 --> 00:45:19,883
- Yeah.
- Not like perfume.

803
00:45:19,967 --> 00:45:22,136
- You know what I mean?
- The person's natural body odor.

804
00:45:22,219 --> 00:45:24,596
- Not a lot of people are aware of it.
- So true.

805
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:26,390
It's not about whether it's good or bad.

806
00:45:26,473 --> 00:45:29,685
I just really think that some people
are compatible and some are not.

807
00:45:29,768 --> 00:45:31,103
Yeah, I agree.

808
00:45:31,186 --> 00:45:32,479
That's actually important.

809
00:45:32,563 --> 00:45:34,022
- Yeah, it really is.
- Yeah.

810
00:45:36,984 --> 00:45:38,819
What else is there?

811
00:45:38,902 --> 00:45:40,112
This is interesting.

812
00:45:43,866 --> 00:45:48,495
I dated a guy once who was extremely
honest about all his flaws,

813
00:45:48,579 --> 00:45:51,457
but because he was so honest
about all of them,

814
00:45:51,540 --> 00:45:53,667
they ended up never feeling like flaws.

815
00:45:53,751 --> 00:45:55,502
- Mm.
- He owned them with confidence.

816
00:45:55,586 --> 00:45:56,628
I can't do that.

817
00:45:59,006 --> 00:46:01,592
Shall we talk about our flaws? One each?

818
00:46:04,136 --> 00:46:05,179
Flaws?

819
00:46:05,763 --> 00:46:09,516
But thinking about it in this way
makes me feel like I have so many of them.

820
00:46:10,642 --> 00:46:12,269
I can't think of many now.

821
00:46:14,396 --> 00:46:16,356
Shall I just tell you mine?

822
00:46:20,444 --> 00:46:21,361
Actually, for me,

823
00:46:21,445 --> 00:46:24,698
I found that being in a relationship
is when things really hit me,

824
00:46:24,782 --> 00:46:26,992
and I end up making
big changes in my life.

825
00:46:27,075 --> 00:46:29,578
- Oh.
- I learn the most about myself

826
00:46:29,661 --> 00:46:32,956
- when I'm in a solid relationship.
- They can change you a lot.

827
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:36,168
But I think I always learn
what my rock bottom is as well.

828
00:46:38,212 --> 00:46:41,131
Are you a good person?

829
00:46:43,300 --> 00:46:44,384
Do you think you are?

830
00:46:46,804 --> 00:46:48,847
I guess I might not be to some people.

831
00:46:48,931 --> 00:46:51,683
I think I would give
the exact same answer.

832
00:46:53,393 --> 00:46:55,229
I feel like I have a lot of really honest

833
00:46:55,312 --> 00:46:58,232
conversations with you
whenever we talk together.

834
00:46:58,315 --> 00:46:59,525
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

835
00:47:00,734 --> 00:47:02,319
I talk about myself a lot.

836
00:47:05,405 --> 00:47:08,325
Then I think it's about time you add me
to the list of guys you like.

837
00:47:08,951 --> 00:47:11,620
- Okay, I will.
- Great. Thanks so much.

838
00:47:12,329 --> 00:47:13,205
Sure.

839
00:47:18,085 --> 00:47:19,211
This is fun.

840
00:47:22,047 --> 00:47:24,091
Mm.

841
00:47:24,174 --> 00:47:25,509
Oh, boy.

842
00:47:25,592 --> 00:47:28,178
See, I don't think it is Sung-min.

843
00:47:28,262 --> 00:47:30,013
If we look at what's going on here,

844
00:47:30,097 --> 00:47:33,642
Sung-min's been very clear
about his feelings for her from the start.

845
00:47:33,725 --> 00:47:37,145
I-geon has never told her clearly
and directly about his feelings.

846
00:47:37,229 --> 00:47:39,690
I think this conversation
could be the catalyst for Go-eun

847
00:47:39,773 --> 00:47:42,067
to change her mind on the situation.

848
00:47:42,150 --> 00:47:43,652
I think it's now up to I-geon

849
00:47:43,735 --> 00:47:46,530
- to win Go-eun over once and for all.
- Yeah.

850
00:47:46,613 --> 00:47:48,282
Right now, she's saying it's Sung-min.

851
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:51,159
Yes, right now she's saying it's Sung-min,
but it's up to I-geon.

852
00:47:51,243 --> 00:47:54,329
- Her feelings could change.
- There's a good chance.

853
00:47:54,413 --> 00:47:55,998
- Yeah.
- Mm.

854
00:48:00,377 --> 00:48:01,295
Yeah?

855
00:48:01,378 --> 00:48:03,672
Do you think it would be okay
if I talked to Su-been?

856
00:48:03,755 --> 00:48:05,340
- Of course. I'm done here.
- Sure.

857
00:48:05,424 --> 00:48:06,758
- She's here.
- Who is it?

858
00:48:06,842 --> 00:48:09,720
- Mina Sue.
- She's at it again.

859
00:48:10,554 --> 00:48:12,890
- I was stopping by.
- Thank you.

860
00:48:12,973 --> 00:48:15,475
- I'm exhausted.
- Hey.

861
00:48:15,559 --> 00:48:17,561
- Hello.
- Did you enjoy your meal?

862
00:48:17,644 --> 00:48:20,147
The meal? The food was awful.
How am I supposed to enjoy it?

863
00:48:20,230 --> 00:48:22,024
- Seriously?
- It's just a greeting.

864
00:48:22,107 --> 00:48:23,984
- A greeting? Thanks.
- Sure.

865
00:48:24,067 --> 00:48:25,319
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

866
00:48:25,402 --> 00:48:26,778
I have a lot to say to you.

867
00:48:26,862 --> 00:48:28,906
- Okay, go ahead.
- Yeah.

868
00:48:28,989 --> 00:48:31,158
And a lot of things to ask you as well.

869
00:48:31,241 --> 00:48:35,329
Like, kind of,
well, first of all, are you okay?

870
00:48:35,412 --> 00:48:38,332
- Sorry?
- I just mean are you okay emotionally?

871
00:48:38,415 --> 00:48:39,541
- Emotionally?
- Yeah.

872
00:48:39,625 --> 00:48:41,418
Yeah, I'm completely fine.

873
00:48:41,501 --> 00:48:42,920
Yeah.

874
00:48:43,003 --> 00:48:44,338
- I'm fine.
- Mm.

875
00:48:45,714 --> 00:48:47,132
Mm.

876
00:48:51,053 --> 00:48:52,179
Why? How are you?

877
00:48:52,262 --> 00:48:55,599
I'm… Well, I don't know, really.

878
00:48:55,682 --> 00:48:58,560
So I went to Paradise with someone else
and you did, too.

879
00:48:58,644 --> 00:48:59,895
- Mm.
- Yeah.

880
00:48:59,978 --> 00:49:01,271
Mm.

881
00:49:02,940 --> 00:49:05,400
I'll be honest,
it took a lot of guts to come.

882
00:49:05,484 --> 00:49:07,569
Yeah. You look like
you've had a change of heart.

883
00:49:07,653 --> 00:49:09,738
Yeah. My pride's really hurt.

884
00:49:09,821 --> 00:49:13,408
- Yeah. I was really jealous.
- Mm.

885
00:49:13,492 --> 00:49:15,410
- Really jealous.
- Mm.

886
00:49:15,494 --> 00:49:16,453
Yesterday?

887
00:49:16,536 --> 00:49:18,956
Yeah. Like, when I was upstairs,

888
00:49:19,039 --> 00:49:21,875
I was able to see the room
we stayed in together.

889
00:49:21,959 --> 00:49:25,587
I didn't see you, obviously,
but I knew it was the same room.

890
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:27,506
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm.

891
00:49:27,589 --> 00:49:28,674
I could see you two

892
00:49:28,757 --> 00:49:31,385
being all lovey-dovey
in the helicopter right next to me.

893
00:49:31,468 --> 00:49:32,678
- Yeah.
- Mm.

894
00:49:33,345 --> 00:49:34,346
And…

895
00:49:35,889 --> 00:49:37,474
Hmm.

896
00:49:37,557 --> 00:49:39,810
I want you to know
you're still on my mind.

897
00:49:39,893 --> 00:49:40,852
Yeah.

898
00:49:41,395 --> 00:49:42,938
But I think you know that,

899
00:49:43,021 --> 00:49:45,107
so I'm sorry for being
kind of mean to you.

900
00:49:45,190 --> 00:49:46,942
I know that I'm being childish.

901
00:49:47,025 --> 00:49:50,320
I admit that I'm being childish,
and I'm sorry for that.

902
00:49:50,404 --> 00:49:52,864
I'm older than you.
I shouldn't be acting like…

903
00:49:52,948 --> 00:49:55,450
- Oh, no, no.
- So I'm really sorry.

904
00:49:55,534 --> 00:49:59,413
And, well, I do think about you a lot.

905
00:49:59,496 --> 00:50:01,581
- Right.
- But I…

906
00:50:01,665 --> 00:50:05,252
The way I've been acting
towards you recently and treating you,

907
00:50:06,545 --> 00:50:08,714
I swear I won't do that anymore.

908
00:50:08,797 --> 00:50:10,882
- Mm.
- Mm.

909
00:50:10,966 --> 00:50:12,968
- Oh.
- Ah.

910
00:50:13,051 --> 00:50:13,927
What?

911
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:16,847
I won't do that anymore.

912
00:50:16,930 --> 00:50:19,349
- Mm.
- Mm.

913
00:50:19,433 --> 00:50:22,769
Because I know there are girls
you're getting to know,

914
00:50:22,853 --> 00:50:25,397
and I can tell you two look
really good together.

915
00:50:25,480 --> 00:50:28,692
And although there's still some time
left here to make decisions

916
00:50:28,775 --> 00:50:31,486
or have more conversations,
that's what I'm going to do.

917
00:50:31,570 --> 00:50:33,238
And I just wanted to tell you that.

918
00:50:33,321 --> 00:50:36,199
Well, thanks for telling me
and letting me know.

919
00:50:36,992 --> 00:50:38,827
I should have told you this sooner.

920
00:50:39,786 --> 00:50:42,706
But, you know, after we got back
from Paradise the first time,

921
00:50:42,789 --> 00:50:45,208
- I spent a lot of time with Hee-sun.
- Mm.

922
00:50:45,292 --> 00:50:47,502
And I went to Paradise with her yesterday.

923
00:50:48,462 --> 00:50:51,131
And after all that,
I think I'm liking her more and more.

924
00:50:51,214 --> 00:50:52,591
- Mm.
- Yeah.

925
00:50:52,674 --> 00:50:54,718
My feelings for her have grown a lot,

926
00:50:54,801 --> 00:50:57,429
so I haven't been able
to pay much attention.

927
00:50:57,512 --> 00:51:00,098
No, I actually really like that
about you, though.

928
00:51:00,182 --> 00:51:04,227
Because if you do like someone,
it's only right that you focus on them.

929
00:51:04,311 --> 00:51:06,396
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

930
00:51:06,480 --> 00:51:08,690
And this may sound really selfish of me,

931
00:51:08,774 --> 00:51:11,068
but looking back on this whole experience,

932
00:51:11,151 --> 00:51:14,279
I think there was always someone
who was looking out for me.

933
00:51:14,362 --> 00:51:16,656
- Mm.
- Sung-hun's always looked out for me.

934
00:51:16,740 --> 00:51:17,824
- Right, right.
- Mm.

935
00:51:17,908 --> 00:51:20,035
- Exactly.
- No way. Sung-hun?

936
00:51:20,118 --> 00:51:21,703
Oh, wow.

937
00:51:21,787 --> 00:51:23,997
I feel like
I should be paying more attention

938
00:51:24,081 --> 00:51:28,210
to the person who is actually expressing
his feelings for me like that,

939
00:51:28,293 --> 00:51:30,420
and, you know,
get to know him better instead.

940
00:51:30,504 --> 00:51:32,923
Yeah. I'll totally root for you on that.

941
00:51:33,507 --> 00:51:36,593
But I really am sorry
that I didn't tell you sooner.

942
00:51:36,676 --> 00:51:38,011
No, it's okay.

943
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:42,182
I also feel bad about what happened
at the campfire thing, so yeah.

944
00:51:42,265 --> 00:51:44,309
- Let's just forget about it.
- Yeah.

945
00:51:44,392 --> 00:51:46,812
We should never feel bad
about what happens here.

946
00:51:46,895 --> 00:51:47,854
- Exactly.
- Mm.

947
00:51:47,938 --> 00:51:50,565
We don't need to ignore each other.
We can still joke around.

948
00:51:50,649 --> 00:51:53,068
No, I never ignored you.
At the end of the day--

949
00:51:53,151 --> 00:51:55,028
- I mean, going forward from here.
- Of course.

950
00:51:55,112 --> 00:51:57,155
- That goes without saying.
- Exactly.

951
00:51:57,239 --> 00:51:59,991
I really do have so much affection
for you as a person.

952
00:52:00,075 --> 00:52:02,410
You were the first guy
I went to Paradise with.

953
00:52:02,494 --> 00:52:03,662
I care about you a lot.

954
00:52:03,745 --> 00:52:06,832
You're a good person,
and I'm really grateful to you.

955
00:52:06,915 --> 00:52:09,334
- I really am.
- Me, too. Yeah.

956
00:52:09,417 --> 00:52:12,170
Okay. I'll leave you
to have conversations with Hee-sun,

957
00:52:12,254 --> 00:52:13,463
- or whoever else.
- Yeah.

958
00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:15,382
Today is gonna be an important day.

959
00:52:16,091 --> 00:52:17,717
Whoa.

960
00:52:17,801 --> 00:52:20,720
- What brought on this change of heart?
- I'm not sure.

961
00:52:20,804 --> 00:52:22,806
Maybe Min-gee's words
have had an impact on her.

962
00:52:22,889 --> 00:52:25,016
Maybe they gave her the push she needed.

963
00:52:25,100 --> 00:52:26,560
I really feel like that could be it.

964
00:52:26,643 --> 00:52:29,062
I feel like watching
<i>Single's Inferno </i>right now

965
00:52:29,146 --> 00:52:31,022
is like watching Mina Sue's growth story.

966
00:52:31,106 --> 00:52:33,859
What Mina Sue did just now was so cool.

967
00:52:33,942 --> 00:52:36,027
- I'm proud of her.
- She was like the female lead

968
00:52:36,111 --> 00:52:40,782
in one of those American foreign movies
or TV shows saying her final goodbyes.

969
00:52:40,866 --> 00:52:44,286
- That was so cool.
- This must be the end of it, right?

970
00:52:46,538 --> 00:52:48,331
- Right?
- Yeah. I think so.

971
00:52:48,415 --> 00:52:51,168
Things seem to be ending
on a good note this season, don't they?

972
00:52:51,251 --> 00:52:53,336
- This has to be the end.
- Don't you think?

973
00:52:53,420 --> 00:52:56,173
Su-been just told her his feelings
for Hee-sun have been growing.

974
00:52:56,256 --> 00:52:57,799
He's made it clear, so it's over.

975
00:52:57,883 --> 00:53:00,427
If she can't let go after this,
then seriously?

976
00:53:00,510 --> 00:53:03,346
What I also love about this
is she seems to acknowledge

977
00:53:03,430 --> 00:53:05,390
that Sung-hun's always been there for her.

978
00:53:05,473 --> 00:53:07,475
And she's finally
admitting that to herself.

979
00:53:07,559 --> 00:53:10,228
- Mina Sue has turned over a new leaf.
- All good now.

980
00:53:10,312 --> 00:53:13,190
Given how great she was now,
let's all give her a round of applause.

981
00:53:13,273 --> 00:53:16,651
- Mina, nicely done. Congratulations.
- Nicely done, Mina Sue.

982
00:53:16,735 --> 00:53:18,945
Very nice, bravo. Well done.

983
00:53:19,029 --> 00:53:21,198
Yeah, we had
the wrong idea about Mina Sue.

984
00:53:21,281 --> 00:53:23,283
Yeah, we had the wrong idea.

985
00:53:23,366 --> 00:53:25,285
We've watched her grow
into an amazing person.

986
00:53:25,368 --> 00:53:28,538
- Growth comes from mistakes.
- You're the best, Mina Sue.

987
00:53:34,711 --> 00:53:36,922
So, what did you talk about with Su-been?

988
00:53:37,005 --> 00:53:39,299
- They're finally talking.
- Seung-il and Min-gee.

989
00:53:39,382 --> 00:53:41,885
Yes, come on. Untangle this mess.

990
00:53:41,968 --> 00:53:45,764
Me? Oh, just this and that.
I'll let you talk first.

991
00:53:45,847 --> 00:53:47,849
You said you figured things out
after the trip.

992
00:53:47,933 --> 00:53:48,975
That's right.

993
00:53:49,059 --> 00:53:51,895
Mm. Yeah. I mean, yesterday was good.

994
00:53:51,978 --> 00:53:53,396
- It was fun.
- Mm.

995
00:53:53,480 --> 00:53:55,774
We talked a lot.

996
00:53:55,857 --> 00:53:57,734
And I always thought
she was an awesome person.

997
00:53:57,817 --> 00:53:59,653
- Mm.
- But…

998
00:54:02,989 --> 00:54:03,990
I'm not sure.

999
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:08,495
So the same then.
Aren't you also not sure about me?

1000
00:54:08,578 --> 00:54:13,291
It's just that when I'm with her,
the proper thing to do is focus on her.

1001
00:54:13,375 --> 00:54:15,293
- True.
- I did my best not to think about you.

1002
00:54:15,377 --> 00:54:17,754
- Of course, that's easier said than done.
- Mm.

1003
00:54:19,631 --> 00:54:23,218
- But on the helicopter back…
- Mm.

1004
00:54:23,301 --> 00:54:25,262
- I was lost in thought.
- About me?

1005
00:54:25,345 --> 00:54:29,474
Yeah, I don't know why,
because I'm still myself with Mina.

1006
00:54:29,557 --> 00:54:32,686
I've realized that the happiest
and most comfortable side of me

1007
00:54:32,769 --> 00:54:34,729
only comes out when I'm with you.

1008
00:54:34,813 --> 00:54:37,732
- Mm.
- Those were the kinds of thoughts

1009
00:54:37,816 --> 00:54:40,151
going through my mind
on the helicopter ride back.

1010
00:54:40,235 --> 00:54:42,112
And now, I'm certain.

1011
00:54:42,195 --> 00:54:45,865
I've reached the conclusion that
there's no second choice for me anymore.

1012
00:54:47,367 --> 00:54:49,995
- There's no second choice at all.
- Mm.

1013
00:54:54,124 --> 00:54:57,210
So not to pressure you, but…

1014
00:55:01,131 --> 00:55:05,510
Let's go together again to Paradise.

1015
00:55:11,891 --> 00:55:15,228
- Aw!
- She's about to cry.

1016
00:55:15,312 --> 00:55:18,398
- She seriously is.
- I mean, even I'm about to cry.

1017
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:24,863
I'll never give you mixed signals again.

1018
00:55:31,619 --> 00:55:32,871
<i>I was happy.</i>

1019
00:55:32,954 --> 00:55:35,081
It was the answer
I'd been hoping for all along.

1020
00:55:35,165 --> 00:55:38,293
But all the heartache I'd suffered
flashed through my mind,

1021
00:55:38,376 --> 00:55:40,545
and I started feeling all these emotions.

1022
00:55:40,628 --> 00:55:42,756
It was a bit of a struggle in that moment.

1023
00:55:44,716 --> 00:55:45,842
Mentally.

1024
00:55:46,426 --> 00:55:48,970
- So, do you need some time to think or…
- Me?

1025
00:55:49,554 --> 00:55:51,348
I'm happiest when I'm with you.

1026
00:55:51,848 --> 00:55:54,809
I'm happiest when I'm with you.

1027
00:55:54,893 --> 00:55:57,812
I'm happy, too.
That's why I'm back here with you.

1028
00:55:59,814 --> 00:56:00,648
I like you.

1029
00:56:00,732 --> 00:56:04,402
But you cause me to have
some crazy mood swings sometimes,

1030
00:56:04,486 --> 00:56:07,530
and I really don't like that about myself.

1031
00:56:08,531 --> 00:56:12,619
Actually, when you told me you were gonna
talk to Su-been first, I was like, "Mm."

1032
00:56:14,829 --> 00:56:16,956
That was a weird feeling for me.

1033
00:56:17,040 --> 00:56:20,627
I thought, "The way I'm feeling now,
Min-gee must have felt even worse."

1034
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:23,630
I'm really glad you realized.

1035
00:56:23,713 --> 00:56:25,006
Hey, at least I realized it.

1036
00:56:25,090 --> 00:56:27,550
Not like,
"Oh, she's talking to someone else.

1037
00:56:27,634 --> 00:56:29,886
I guess I'll come back later."

1038
00:56:29,969 --> 00:56:32,597
"Okay, it's no big deal.
I'll just come back later."

1039
00:56:32,680 --> 00:56:36,351
At least I'm not one of those guys.
You should be happy I'm not like that.

1040
00:56:38,061 --> 00:56:38,978
Ah!

1041
00:56:44,025 --> 00:56:46,736
- She's been through the wringer.
- I'm tearing up.

1042
00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:47,862
- Are you crying?
- No.

1043
00:56:47,946 --> 00:56:50,448
- Are you crying?
- No, I'm not crying.

1044
00:56:50,532 --> 00:56:54,327
But I am a bit choked up because I know
exactly what she's been through.

1045
00:56:54,411 --> 00:56:56,413
- Another round of applause.
- Here, here.

1046
00:56:56,496 --> 00:56:59,666
- You've been through a lot.
- With that, we're cutting this season

1047
00:56:59,749 --> 00:57:02,710
of <i>Single's Inferno </i>short.
That's it, folks.

1048
00:57:02,794 --> 00:57:05,922
- This feels like the last episode.
- End it on this beautiful note.

1049
00:57:06,005 --> 00:57:07,924
- It's got last episode vibes.
- Why is there more?

1050
00:57:08,007 --> 00:57:09,384
Why is there much left?

1051
00:57:09,467 --> 00:57:11,803
Is it just going to be
flashbacks from now on?

1052
00:57:11,886 --> 00:57:13,680
A spin-off, a spin-off.

1053
00:57:13,763 --> 00:57:15,640
How are they doing in the real world?

1054
00:57:15,723 --> 00:57:17,934
- "Where are they now?" segment.
- Yeah.

1055
00:57:22,397 --> 00:57:27,152
<i>We will now begin</i>
<i>the Paradise-bound couple matching.</i>

1056
00:57:28,027 --> 00:57:31,406
<i>Those who have won a date to Paradise</i>
<i>from winning the girls' game,</i>

1057
00:57:31,489 --> 00:57:36,411
<i>Kim Min-gee, Lee Joo-young</i>
<i>and Park Hee-sun, make your way outside.</i>

1058
00:57:36,494 --> 00:57:37,954
- See you later.
- See you later.

1059
00:57:38,037 --> 00:57:39,873
Bye. See you later.

1060
00:57:40,623 --> 00:57:43,918
Ugh. I really needed to go today.

1061
00:57:44,002 --> 00:57:47,797
Yeah, well, I really thought
I'd be the one going today.

1062
00:57:47,881 --> 00:57:49,549
- Is that it?
- Have a good trip.

1063
00:57:49,632 --> 00:57:52,510
- Are you okay?
- Hee-sun will pick you again.

1064
00:57:52,594 --> 00:57:54,262
It's gonna be you and Seung-il.

1065
00:57:55,889 --> 00:57:59,517
I assume the couple matching
will go exactly how we've imagined it.

1066
00:57:59,601 --> 00:58:01,936
- Yes.
- Min-gee will definitely choose Seung-il.

1067
00:58:02,020 --> 00:58:03,229
They're all set.

1068
00:58:03,313 --> 00:58:06,941
- And Joo-young?
- I don't know about Joo-young.

1069
00:58:07,025 --> 00:58:09,319
- I think Jae-jin might go.
- Yeah.

1070
00:58:09,402 --> 00:58:12,906
I have a slight question mark
because things went well with Hyun-jae.

1071
00:58:12,989 --> 00:58:15,783
- Yeah. Hee-sun will choose Su-been.
- Yeah.

1072
00:58:15,867 --> 00:58:17,702
I can't think
of any possible curveballs here.

1073
00:58:17,785 --> 00:58:19,954
- No, exactly.
- Me neither.

1074
00:58:21,623 --> 00:58:24,042
<i>Starting with Kim Min-gee in first place,</i>

1075
00:58:24,125 --> 00:58:28,505
<i>please select the person you would like</i>
<i>to go on a date with in Paradise.</i>

1076
00:58:30,673 --> 00:58:34,177
She might do something.
Something totally unexpected.

1077
00:58:36,221 --> 00:58:38,765
Is your mind totally
made up now, Seung-il?

1078
00:58:38,848 --> 00:58:41,559
- When we were talking earlier…
- You settled everything?

1079
00:58:41,643 --> 00:58:43,728
- Yeah. So I have a pretty good idea.
- Right.

1080
00:58:43,811 --> 00:58:45,146
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

1081
00:58:45,230 --> 00:58:48,274
- Seung-il's already packed his bags.
- Yeah, exactly. Look at him.

1082
00:58:48,358 --> 00:58:49,901
He's all set to go.

1083
00:58:51,444 --> 00:58:54,948
The person I would like
to go to Paradise with is…

1084
00:59:08,836 --> 00:59:10,755
Lim Su-been.

1085
00:59:10,838 --> 00:59:12,173
What?!

1086
00:59:12,257 --> 00:59:14,551
- Huh?
- Hold on. I've got chills.

1087
00:59:14,634 --> 00:59:17,011
- Huh?
- What did she just do?

1088
00:59:17,971 --> 00:59:20,473
Wait, seriously, I'm getting
full body chills right now.

1089
00:59:20,557 --> 00:59:21,891
I got chills, too.

1090
00:59:21,975 --> 00:59:23,184
What?

1091
00:59:23,268 --> 00:59:24,852
What?

1092
00:59:24,936 --> 00:59:28,064
- I'm so shocked, I can't speak.
- What is this?

1093
00:59:28,147 --> 00:59:30,817
So now that Mina Sue has come
to her senses, Min-gee's gone nuts?

1094
00:59:30,900 --> 00:59:32,902
A demon is jumping
from one person to another.

1095
00:59:32,986 --> 00:59:36,698
- What's going on?
- The demon must be possessing people.

1096
00:59:36,781 --> 00:59:39,284
You know what, it possessed her
when they were talking.

1097
00:59:39,367 --> 00:59:42,036
- When she touched her shoulder.
- This makes no sense.

1098
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,913
What is this? What's going on?

1099
00:59:43,997 --> 00:59:46,165
This is so shocking to everyone here.

1100
00:59:46,249 --> 00:59:48,167
This is why there are more episodes.

1101
00:59:48,251 --> 00:59:51,296
This is why this can't be the
final episode. This is the reason.

1102
00:59:51,379 --> 00:59:53,965
Even the background music
sounded like the final episode.

1103
00:59:54,048 --> 00:59:56,926
- I'm absolutely dying to know why.
- Me, too.

1104
00:59:57,010 --> 00:59:59,345
Please make it make sense.

1105
00:59:59,429 --> 01:00:01,014
Lim Su-been.

1106
01:00:07,854 --> 01:00:10,565
<i>Kim Min-gee has made her selection…</i>

1107
01:00:12,275 --> 01:00:14,527
<i>Lim Su-been.</i>

1108
01:00:14,611 --> 01:00:19,365
<i>Kim Min-gee and Lim Su-been,</i>
<i>please hold hands and leave for Paradise.</i>

1109
01:00:20,241 --> 01:00:22,118
- See you guys later.
- Bye.

1110
01:00:28,291 --> 01:00:30,126
<i>I struggled a lot with the decision,</i>

1111
01:00:30,209 --> 01:00:34,422
but I, kind of, resented Seung-il
because he truly put me through hell.

1112
01:00:34,505 --> 01:00:38,468
So I wanted to see if I could still
set aside everything he put me through.

1113
01:00:38,551 --> 01:00:41,721
And whether I'd still think of him
even when I was happy

1114
01:00:41,804 --> 01:00:46,434
and enjoying myself in Paradise,
would I still miss him?

1115
01:00:46,517 --> 01:00:48,603
That's what I wanted
to find out this trip.

1116
01:00:49,270 --> 01:00:52,732
And I realized, after talking with him,
that I have been curious about Su-been,

1117
01:00:52,815 --> 01:00:55,360
even though it hasn't been
a strong curiosity.

1118
01:00:55,443 --> 01:00:56,402
YESTERDAY AFTERNOON

1119
01:00:56,486 --> 01:00:59,238
You know how we were talking
while playing Halli Galli?

1120
01:00:59,322 --> 01:01:01,282
Some things made me go, "Oh, oh, oh."

1121
01:01:01,366 --> 01:01:02,742
- We seem similar?
- Yeah.

1122
01:01:02,825 --> 01:01:04,911
I also heard that you like honest people,

1123
01:01:04,994 --> 01:01:07,497
and I thought that
we might have similar values,

1124
01:01:07,580 --> 01:01:09,749
so I wanted to have
a conversation with you.

1125
01:01:09,832 --> 01:01:12,710
- Totally. Yeah.
- First of all, your looks are just…

1126
01:01:12,794 --> 01:01:14,712
Wow.

1127
01:01:14,796 --> 01:01:16,464
I think I said in my first confessional,

1128
01:01:16,547 --> 01:01:19,634
they asked me if there was anyone I liked,
anyone I was interested in,

1129
01:01:19,717 --> 01:01:22,887
and I said, "Oh, Su-been
is totally my type, looks-wise."

1130
01:01:22,970 --> 01:01:24,389
Really?

1131
01:01:25,098 --> 01:01:29,143
Hee-sun has priority, so I made sure
to ask for her permission first.

1132
01:01:29,227 --> 01:01:30,812
THIS MORNING

1133
01:01:30,895 --> 01:01:34,357
<i>I actually want to know if Seung-il is</i>
<i>sure about me at all or if he's moved on.</i>

1134
01:01:34,440 --> 01:01:35,983
<i>That's why I want to talk to Su-been.</i>

1135
01:01:36,067 --> 01:01:37,610
Okay.

1136
01:01:37,694 --> 01:01:38,611
Go ahead.

1137
01:01:39,570 --> 01:01:43,282
- How are you so chill about it?
- Hey, wait a second.

1138
01:01:43,366 --> 01:01:45,368
I mean, seriously.

1139
01:01:45,451 --> 01:01:48,663
Well, okay, actually, hearing that,
I see where she's coming from.

1140
01:01:48,746 --> 01:01:51,749
Because Seung-il did take a long time
to make his mind up, too.

1141
01:01:51,833 --> 01:01:53,501
I get that she's curious about Su-been,

1142
01:01:53,584 --> 01:01:55,545
but does she really need
to be with another person

1143
01:01:55,628 --> 01:01:57,714
to confirm her feelings for someone?

1144
01:01:57,797 --> 01:01:59,257
I think that's just an excuse.

1145
01:01:59,340 --> 01:02:02,260
What's really going on is that Min-gee
had a second option after all.

1146
01:02:02,343 --> 01:02:04,595
She just wanted to go with Su-been.

1147
01:02:06,097 --> 01:02:07,849
- Hello.
- Hello, Su-been.

1148
01:02:07,932 --> 01:02:08,808
Hello.

1149
01:02:08,891 --> 01:02:10,810
Shall we head out?

1150
01:02:10,893 --> 01:02:12,770
- Okay, let's go.
- Yes, let's go.

1151
01:02:14,480 --> 01:02:16,524
Fine. Go.

1152
01:02:16,607 --> 01:02:18,025
- "Fine. Go."
- See ya.

1153
01:02:20,111 --> 01:02:22,780
Personally, I think
he and I are both pretty certain

1154
01:02:22,864 --> 01:02:25,283
of our feelings for each other,
so I'm not that nervous.

1155
01:02:25,366 --> 01:02:27,326
And that's why I was okay with it.

1156
01:02:27,952 --> 01:02:30,163
- That's an interesting combo.
- I know, right?

1157
01:02:30,246 --> 01:02:33,458
I think the Seung-il going
with me yesterday hit her pretty hard.

1158
01:02:34,000 --> 01:02:36,627
- Is she trying to provoke Seung-il?
- It's possible.

1159
01:02:36,711 --> 01:02:38,129
- Really?
- I have chills.

1160
01:02:39,589 --> 01:02:41,758
I'm ticked off they're holding hands.

1161
01:02:43,634 --> 01:02:45,052
I'm totally pissed.

1162
01:02:45,136 --> 01:02:47,096
I haven't held hands with anyone yet.

1163
01:02:47,180 --> 01:02:49,056
I'm annoyed she's doing it before me.

1164
01:02:49,766 --> 01:02:52,059
Man, you have a lot on your mind.

1165
01:02:55,354 --> 01:02:58,065
See, it's working.
It's already eating away at him.

1166
01:03:00,067 --> 01:03:01,027
This is necessary.

1167
01:03:01,110 --> 01:03:04,113
You shouldn't always be available,
sitting around, waiting for this.

1168
01:03:04,197 --> 01:03:05,531
This is really tough.

1169
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:07,825
Min-gee seems to be
a sucker for good looks.

1170
01:03:07,909 --> 01:03:10,912
- So something might happen there.
- Stop. There's no way.

1171
01:03:10,995 --> 01:03:13,623
Remember, Su-been's mind
is firmly made up, though,

1172
01:03:13,706 --> 01:03:16,250
so I don't think there will be
any chemistry there.

1173
01:03:18,252 --> 01:03:21,297
<i>Next up is Lee Joo-young in second place.</i>

1174
01:03:21,380 --> 01:03:26,219
<i>Please select the person you would</i>
<i>like to go on a date with in Paradise.</i>

1175
01:03:36,521 --> 01:03:39,524
The person I would like
to go to Paradise with is…

1176
01:03:41,818 --> 01:03:44,904
<i>Lee Joo-young has made her selection.</i>

1177
01:03:53,287 --> 01:03:55,206
<i>Kim Jae-jin.</i>

1178
01:03:55,289 --> 01:04:00,419
<i>Lee Joo-young and Kim Jae-jin,</i>
<i>please hold hands and leave for Paradise.</i>

1179
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:01,462
See you later.

1180
01:04:01,546 --> 01:04:03,339
- Have fun.
- See you later.

1181
01:04:03,422 --> 01:04:04,757
See you later.

1182
01:04:08,010 --> 01:04:09,762
Bye.

1183
01:04:09,846 --> 01:04:12,557
See you.

1184
01:04:30,783 --> 01:04:32,410
- Hello.
- Pleased to meet you.

1185
01:04:32,493 --> 01:04:34,412
Right, your hand.

1186
01:04:39,417 --> 01:04:41,711
This is nice.

1187
01:04:41,794 --> 01:04:44,964
- You happy?
- Really happy.

1188
01:04:47,091 --> 01:04:50,303
<i>Lastly, Park Hee-sun in third place.</i>

1189
01:04:50,386 --> 01:04:55,099
<i>Please select the person you would like</i>
<i>to go on a date with in Paradise.</i>

1190
01:04:55,808 --> 01:04:58,102
- I don't know who Hee-sun will pick.
- Who could it be?

1191
01:04:58,185 --> 01:04:59,896
You're right. Hmm.

1192
01:04:59,979 --> 01:05:01,647
Who's Hee-sun going to pick?

1193
01:05:01,731 --> 01:05:04,901
Oh, yeah. I guess she'll just go
with someone she's curious about.

1194
01:05:08,988 --> 01:05:11,908
I wonder who she'll go with.
I'm really curious.

1195
01:05:13,034 --> 01:05:14,452
Eh.

1196
01:05:14,535 --> 01:05:16,120
I really don't know.

1197
01:05:19,248 --> 01:05:21,834
The person I would like
to go to Paradise with is…

1198
01:05:23,336 --> 01:05:25,046
Is Hyun-jae.

1199
01:05:25,129 --> 01:05:26,464
- Hyun-jae?
- Really?

1200
01:05:27,798 --> 01:05:29,133
Why Hyun-jae?

1201
01:05:29,216 --> 01:05:31,510
Stop projecting
your own feelings onto this.

1202
01:05:31,594 --> 01:05:32,845
Hey, those aren't my feelings.

1203
01:05:32,929 --> 01:05:34,430
- What's wrong with you?
- Right.

1204
01:05:36,599 --> 01:05:39,769
Although, Hyun-jae
does have similarities to Su-been.

1205
01:05:39,852 --> 01:05:42,188
Man, no one's a great fit for this one.

1206
01:05:42,271 --> 01:05:44,398
Sung-hun because he hasn't been yet.

1207
01:05:44,482 --> 01:05:45,775
It has to be him.

1208
01:05:45,858 --> 01:05:48,027
I don't think she'll pick him
just to save him.

1209
01:05:48,110 --> 01:05:50,404
- That would be a disaster for Sung-hun.
- Sung-hun?

1210
01:05:50,488 --> 01:05:53,449
When he finally has a chance
to get something going with Mina Sue.

1211
01:05:53,532 --> 01:05:56,077
Oh, you're right.
I hope not, this could be bad.

1212
01:05:56,160 --> 01:06:00,081
- That'll mess things up again.
- I really doubt it. Those two?

1213
01:06:01,374 --> 01:06:04,251
The person I would like
to go to Paradise with is…

1214
01:06:05,419 --> 01:06:07,505
Who will Hee-sun choose this time?

1215
01:06:07,588 --> 01:06:08,965
I'm really curious, actually.

1216
01:06:09,048 --> 01:06:11,050
Yeah, I bet it's a tough choice for her.

1217
01:06:11,133 --> 01:06:12,218
Yeah.

1218
01:06:24,146 --> 01:06:25,773
Lee Sung-hun.

1219
01:06:26,983 --> 01:06:28,651
I told you!

1220
01:06:28,734 --> 01:06:29,819
But why?

1221
01:06:30,403 --> 01:06:32,196
- Wow.
- Wow, just when he's…

1222
01:06:32,279 --> 01:06:34,824
- Wow, I'm shocked.
- This can't be.

1223
01:06:34,907 --> 01:06:38,119
Just when he's about to get
something going with Mina Sue.

1224
01:06:38,202 --> 01:06:39,662
<i>Lee Sung-hun.</i>

1225
01:06:41,163 --> 01:06:44,083
<i>Lee Sung-hun,</i>
<i>please make your way outside.</i>

1226
01:06:44,166 --> 01:06:45,418
See you later.

1227
01:06:45,501 --> 01:06:46,711
Bye.

1228
01:06:48,212 --> 01:06:49,588
<i>Lee Sung-hun.</i>

1229
01:06:51,048 --> 01:06:53,968
<i>Lee Sung-hun,</i>
<i>please make your way outside.</i>

1230
01:06:59,181 --> 01:07:00,099
Okay. Bye.

1231
01:07:06,897 --> 01:07:08,149
Oh, there it is.

1232
01:07:10,067 --> 01:07:12,319
- Hello.
- Hi.

1233
01:07:12,820 --> 01:07:14,238
Let's go.

1234
01:07:15,573 --> 01:07:16,532
Let's go.

1235
01:07:18,367 --> 01:07:20,703
I guess it's gonna be awkward
in the helicopter.

1236
01:07:20,786 --> 01:07:22,163
Why? It's all fine.

1237
01:07:22,246 --> 01:07:23,414
- Oh, yeah? Okay.
- Yeah.

1238
01:07:23,497 --> 01:07:26,459
Before all this happened,
I said I wanted to go with you today.

1239
01:07:26,542 --> 01:07:28,669
- Really?
- Even if I were in first place,

1240
01:07:28,753 --> 01:07:30,254
this would be my decision.

1241
01:07:30,838 --> 01:07:33,674
- Hey, is this the right way?
- Yeah, we get on here.

1242
01:07:34,967 --> 01:07:38,679
Okay, but she could've done this to
get back at Mina Sue, don't you think?

1243
01:07:38,763 --> 01:07:40,639
- Wait, who? Hee-sun?
- Hee-sun.

1244
01:07:41,348 --> 01:07:43,809
Because Mina Sue
kept coming on to Su-been?

1245
01:07:43,893 --> 01:07:47,897
About 5% of her decision
could have been based on that. Yeah.

1246
01:07:47,980 --> 01:07:51,275
- I'm worried all of a sudden.
- Why?

1247
01:07:51,358 --> 01:07:54,653
I'm suddenly worried
that he'll fall for her.

1248
01:07:54,737 --> 01:07:57,364
No, I don't think
Sung-hun's feelings will change.

1249
01:07:57,448 --> 01:08:00,076
It could. Shall we open
the door and yell to them?

1250
01:08:00,159 --> 01:08:02,495
- See ya.
- See ya.

1251
01:08:03,746 --> 01:08:05,831
I'm so pissed right now.

1252
01:08:05,915 --> 01:08:10,211
I just feel like all of my guys
are being stolen from me one by one.

1253
01:08:10,836 --> 01:08:13,339
- You should've treated them better.
- Look at this.

1254
01:08:13,422 --> 01:08:15,758
Is today the day where
karma finally balances out?

1255
01:08:15,841 --> 01:08:19,011
Min-gee and Hee-sun are getting
the good karma they deserve.

1256
01:08:19,095 --> 01:08:22,556
At least that's what I think is happening.
It's a total reset.

1257
01:08:52,086 --> 01:08:55,089
It's tilting.

1258
01:09:00,052 --> 01:09:00,970
This is fun.

1259
01:09:02,680 --> 01:09:04,765
Don't you think it's leaning
more than usual today?

1260
01:09:04,849 --> 01:09:05,850
I really--

1261
01:09:05,933 --> 01:09:07,810
- I'm curious.
- Sorry?

1262
01:09:07,893 --> 01:09:09,895
I really want to know how old you are.

1263
01:09:14,733 --> 01:09:16,277
You can guess later.

1264
01:09:19,488 --> 01:09:22,533
- Do you like traveling?
- Yeah, I travel a lot.

1265
01:09:22,616 --> 01:09:23,826
Oh.

1266
01:09:23,909 --> 01:09:25,578
Where's your favorite place?

1267
01:09:25,661 --> 01:09:27,913
- Oh, Greece.
- Greece?

1268
01:09:27,997 --> 01:09:31,667
- I want to get married there.
- Oh, do you really? Interesting.

1269
01:09:33,794 --> 01:09:35,254
You know what, after seeing this,

1270
01:09:35,337 --> 01:09:38,007
I actually think Sung-hun
could fall for Hee-sun.

1271
01:09:38,090 --> 01:09:39,717
- No.
- Come on.

1272
01:09:39,800 --> 01:09:41,969
Hee-sun has a different
kind of appeal from Mina Sue.

1273
01:09:42,052 --> 01:09:43,637
She does, but Sung-hun--

1274
01:09:43,721 --> 01:09:47,474
And who says that Sung-hun
can only ever be attracted to Mina Sue?

1275
01:09:48,601 --> 01:09:50,853
PARADISE
PARK HEE-SUN & LEE SUNG-HUN

1276
01:09:50,936 --> 01:09:53,272
I'm starving. I'm gonna eat so much.

1277
01:09:53,355 --> 01:09:54,315
Let's go.

1278
01:09:54,398 --> 01:09:56,650
- It looks so good.
- Okay, let's go.

1279
01:09:56,734 --> 01:09:58,194
Oh, my gosh.

1280
01:09:58,861 --> 01:10:00,112
This is a real feast.

1281
01:10:00,946 --> 01:10:02,281
It looks delicious.

1282
01:10:04,158 --> 01:10:05,868
- Can we eat?
- Yeah.

1283
01:10:05,951 --> 01:10:08,579
- Let me cut it for you first.
- Aw. Thank you.

1284
01:10:14,084 --> 01:10:16,086
- Mm. Thank you.
- Eat up.

1285
01:10:19,048 --> 01:10:20,633
- Any good?
- Yeah.

1286
01:10:20,716 --> 01:10:23,135
- It's so good.
- Let's go.

1287
01:10:25,638 --> 01:10:27,431
Holy!

1288
01:10:27,514 --> 01:10:28,682
Wait, wait.

1289
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:30,684
I know, right?

1290
01:10:30,768 --> 01:10:32,561
Enjoy yourself. You've had such a tough…

1291
01:10:32,645 --> 01:10:34,855
You're right. It's his first time here.

1292
01:10:35,856 --> 01:10:38,150
So tell me about your life from the start.

1293
01:10:38,984 --> 01:10:41,528
- I was born in Korea.
- Mm-hmm.

1294
01:10:41,612 --> 01:10:45,324
Then my family moved to Canada
when I was in fourth grade.

1295
01:10:45,407 --> 01:10:46,700
Whoa!

1296
01:10:47,910 --> 01:10:50,871
And then I went
to university in the States.

1297
01:10:50,955 --> 01:10:53,499
What? Which one?

1298
01:10:53,582 --> 01:10:55,000
Carnegie Mellon.

1299
01:10:55,084 --> 01:10:56,835
- CMU?
- Yeah.

1300
01:10:56,919 --> 01:10:59,004
Whoa, wait.
We definitely have mutuals then.

1301
01:10:59,088 --> 01:11:00,798
- Really? Oh, my God.
- Yeah.

1302
01:11:01,507 --> 01:11:05,719
He seems academic since he said
they must have mutual contacts.

1303
01:11:05,803 --> 01:11:07,596
- Yeah.
- I'm curious.

1304
01:11:07,680 --> 01:11:09,807
I can't believe there's
someone like you at CMU.

1305
01:11:13,018 --> 01:11:14,436
I should have gone there, too.

1306
01:11:16,272 --> 01:11:18,274
- What do you study?
- Mm.

1307
01:11:18,357 --> 01:11:21,986
What's my major? Wait, guess my major.

1308
01:11:22,069 --> 01:11:23,445
Computer science.

1309
01:11:23,529 --> 01:11:24,738
- Computer science?
- Yeah.

1310
01:11:24,822 --> 01:11:25,948
It's similar.

1311
01:11:26,031 --> 01:11:27,866
- Information systems.
- Damn.

1312
01:11:27,950 --> 01:11:29,994
Okay, so you're a total genius.

1313
01:11:31,412 --> 01:11:34,707
I'm guessing other people won't know
when they hear CMU, but I do.

1314
01:11:34,790 --> 01:11:38,127
CMU is really prestigious,
basically one of the top schools.

1315
01:11:38,210 --> 01:11:39,336
Top, like, ten?

1316
01:11:40,004 --> 01:11:41,755
CMU isn't that well known in Korea,

1317
01:11:41,839 --> 01:11:44,049
but it's a highly regarded
school in America.

1318
01:11:44,133 --> 01:11:45,217
Carnegie Mellon.

1319
01:11:45,301 --> 01:11:47,678
- Carnegie Mellon.
- Got it.

1320
01:11:47,761 --> 01:11:51,473
- I know it well actually.
- Mm.

1321
01:11:51,557 --> 01:11:54,310
I was going to go there,
but I ended up going somewhere else.

1322
01:11:54,393 --> 01:11:55,561
Mm.

1323
01:11:55,644 --> 01:11:57,271
What do you think I studied?

1324
01:11:58,522 --> 01:12:01,317
It's too hard.
Guessing would be impossible.

1325
01:12:01,400 --> 01:12:03,986
Okay, you're right.
Math and computer science.

1326
01:12:04,570 --> 01:12:06,447
- He's in STEM, too?
- Oh.

1327
01:12:06,530 --> 01:12:08,073
Math and--

1328
01:12:08,157 --> 01:12:10,075
Math and computer science. Yeah.

1329
01:12:10,159 --> 01:12:12,369
Crazy.

1330
01:12:12,453 --> 01:12:14,246
- We're kind of similar.
- I know.

1331
01:12:14,330 --> 01:12:16,665
I went to college in California,
UC Berkeley.

1332
01:12:16,749 --> 01:12:18,876
Ah.

1333
01:12:18,959 --> 01:12:25,424
And after I graduated, I worked for Google
in California as an AI developer.

1334
01:12:25,507 --> 01:12:28,302
- I worked there for two years.
- Ooh.

1335
01:12:28,385 --> 01:12:31,472
And now, I work in New York
as a hedge-fund trader.

1336
01:12:31,555 --> 01:12:33,640
I'm a trader, quant trader.

1337
01:12:36,143 --> 01:12:38,854
- Wow, that's unexpected.
- Wow.

1338
01:12:39,521 --> 01:12:42,358
<i>I'm a quant trader,</i>
<i>and I live in New York.</i>

1339
01:12:43,317 --> 01:12:45,944
<i>Quant trading is a job</i>
<i>in which you teach computers</i>

1340
01:12:46,028 --> 01:12:50,324
<i>advanced mathematical models</i>
<i>and algorithms to buy and sell stocks.</i>

1341
01:12:50,407 --> 01:12:54,495
<i>I think I got into quant trading</i>
<i>because I like competition.</i>

1342
01:12:56,288 --> 01:12:59,500
<i>When it comes to my field,</i>
<i>I'm totally confident.</i>

1343
01:12:59,583 --> 01:13:02,961
LEE SUNG-HUN
QUANTITATIVE TRADER

1344
01:13:03,045 --> 01:13:04,546
Whoa!

1345
01:13:05,631 --> 01:13:07,257
He teaches computers math?

1346
01:13:07,341 --> 01:13:09,343
I played a quant trader in a show before.

1347
01:13:09,426 --> 01:13:13,097
I know for a fact from doing
so much research that their pay is huge.

1348
01:13:13,180 --> 01:13:15,349
It's basically
director-level kind of stuff.

1349
01:13:15,432 --> 01:13:16,725
This is a massive deal.

1350
01:13:16,809 --> 01:13:19,812
- I really want to know how old he is now.
- So he's a genius.

1351
01:13:19,895 --> 01:13:23,607
He's not the kind of person who would
just sit around pining for Mina Sue.

1352
01:13:23,690 --> 01:13:26,527
I guess that's what happens
when you're stuck on that island.

1353
01:13:26,610 --> 01:13:28,278
- That's right.
- Right?

1354
01:13:28,362 --> 01:13:32,491
I've been working at a hedge fund
as a quant trader for three years now.

1355
01:13:32,574 --> 01:13:35,369
- That's amazing. How interesting.
- Mm.

1356
01:13:35,452 --> 01:13:38,247
- We're kind of similar.
- Yeah, we're really similar.

1357
01:13:38,330 --> 01:13:40,666
- It's like my future.
- Oh, really?

1358
01:13:40,749 --> 01:13:43,669
- Yeah, I can't believe it.
- Oh, okay.

1359
01:13:43,752 --> 01:13:46,130
- Hee-sun, you're a high achiever.
- Yeah.

1360
01:13:47,214 --> 01:13:48,465
You even more so.

1361
01:13:50,134 --> 01:13:52,553
Are you planning on going back
or just forgetting--

1362
01:13:52,636 --> 01:13:54,847
- Yeah, of course I'm going back.
- Mm.

1363
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:57,307
Then I guess
I'll be seeing you when we go back.

1364
01:13:57,391 --> 01:14:00,686
- You live in New York right now, right?
- Yeah. New York currently.

1365
01:14:00,769 --> 01:14:03,021
- Mm. We're so close then.
- Pennsylvania?

1366
01:14:03,105 --> 01:14:04,523
- Yeah.
- Okay.

1367
01:14:04,606 --> 01:14:06,066
By plane, it's one hour?

1368
01:14:06,150 --> 01:14:06,984
Yeah.

1369
01:14:07,484 --> 01:14:08,652
- Right?
- Yeah.

1370
01:14:09,194 --> 01:14:12,322
Wow. I feel so close to you now.

1371
01:14:12,406 --> 01:14:15,159
I mean, I feel like
I now know a lot about you.

1372
01:14:15,242 --> 01:14:17,286
Mm, totally.

1373
01:14:17,369 --> 01:14:18,954
You're only in Korea for a bit?

1374
01:14:19,037 --> 01:14:20,038
- Just for this.
- Wow.

1375
01:14:20,122 --> 01:14:21,582
- Really? Wow.
- Yeah.

1376
01:14:21,665 --> 01:14:25,878
I have a pretty good idea about
your age now, after this conversation.

1377
01:14:25,961 --> 01:14:27,546
'03?

1378
01:14:30,007 --> 01:14:30,966
- Yeah.
- I got it?

1379
01:14:31,049 --> 01:14:32,384
You did.

1380
01:14:33,385 --> 01:14:34,636
How did you get it in one try?

1381
01:14:34,720 --> 01:14:38,182
You said you were a college student,
so I kind of got it right away

1382
01:14:38,265 --> 01:14:40,142
- based off of that information.
- Makes sense.

1383
01:14:40,225 --> 01:14:41,435
Yeah.

1384
01:14:41,518 --> 01:14:42,561
Then you…

1385
01:14:44,354 --> 01:14:49,234
Well, you've been working
post-graduation, so 28?

1386
01:14:49,318 --> 01:14:50,277
You're right.

1387
01:14:50,360 --> 01:14:51,862
'98.

1388
01:14:51,945 --> 01:14:53,238
- Ooh!
- Twenty-eight.

1389
01:14:53,322 --> 01:14:54,948
Mm.

1390
01:14:56,992 --> 01:14:58,410
Am I older than you thought?

1391
01:14:59,369 --> 01:15:01,038
No, it's what I expected.

1392
01:15:01,121 --> 01:15:02,664
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1393
01:15:02,748 --> 01:15:05,292
At first, I thought
you would be really young.

1394
01:15:05,375 --> 01:15:09,421
But then, after talking to you,
you didn't seem young.

1395
01:15:09,505 --> 01:15:13,926
- Mm.
- Because you seem to have experience.

1396
01:15:14,009 --> 01:15:14,968
You're right.

1397
01:15:15,052 --> 01:15:17,554
- I'm older by five years.
- Mm.

1398
01:15:20,516 --> 01:15:22,684
- Interesting, huh?
- I know.

1399
01:15:22,768 --> 01:15:24,853
We have more in common than I thought.

1400
01:15:24,937 --> 01:15:27,231
Just looking at them,
don't you feel some chemistry?

1401
01:15:27,314 --> 01:15:29,316
It feels very balanced and stable.

1402
01:15:29,399 --> 01:15:31,610
- They're both in the US.
- That's right.

1403
01:15:31,693 --> 01:15:33,070
Out of all the couples so far,

1404
01:15:33,153 --> 01:15:35,322
this is easily the couple
with the most potential.

1405
01:15:35,405 --> 01:15:37,616
- You're forgetting something.
- What's that?

1406
01:15:37,699 --> 01:15:39,159
Mina Sue's in the US, too.

1407
01:15:39,243 --> 01:15:41,119
- Wasn't she--
- Ah.

1408
01:15:41,203 --> 01:15:42,621
Wait.

1409
01:15:46,291 --> 01:15:47,334
INFERNO

1410
01:15:47,417 --> 01:15:51,004
Seung-il, where do your feelings stand?

1411
01:15:51,088 --> 01:15:52,756
I'm all in on Min-gee.

1412
01:15:52,839 --> 01:15:56,802
This is one of those cases where
going there confirmed your feelings?

1413
01:15:56,885 --> 01:16:00,514
- Yeah. That's why I wanted to go.
- Because you wanted clarity,

1414
01:16:00,597 --> 01:16:03,141
you thought going there
would give you the answers.

1415
01:16:03,225 --> 01:16:05,227
I felt I had to go there to know for sure.

1416
01:16:05,310 --> 01:16:08,313
And did you guys manage
to have a real talk today?

1417
01:16:08,397 --> 01:16:10,691
Since there was another
couples matching right away,

1418
01:16:10,774 --> 01:16:12,067
I thought I should talk to her.

1419
01:16:12,150 --> 01:16:14,236
But something really weird happened.

1420
01:16:14,319 --> 01:16:15,737
I ran into them right there.

1421
01:16:15,821 --> 01:16:20,033
Min-gee was asking Su-been to chat,
and I just had this weird feeling, so…

1422
01:16:20,117 --> 01:16:21,577
- Wait, today?
- Earlier today.

1423
01:16:21,660 --> 01:16:23,704
- So I was like, "Hmm."
- Were you aware of it?

1424
01:16:23,787 --> 01:16:24,955
That was the first.

1425
01:16:25,038 --> 01:16:26,707
So you had no idea she would do that?

1426
01:16:26,790 --> 01:16:29,710
- No clue she was interested in Su-been.
- Oh, wow.

1427
01:16:29,793 --> 01:16:32,337
So I was like, "Okay,"
and we were talking.

1428
01:16:34,131 --> 01:16:36,633
And to be honest,
I was feeling pretty confident.

1429
01:16:36,717 --> 01:16:38,594
Not confident that she'd choose me,

1430
01:16:38,677 --> 01:16:41,722
but confident because
I felt I'd done all that I could.

1431
01:16:41,805 --> 01:16:43,599
I was thinking about it again in the room.

1432
01:16:43,682 --> 01:16:47,477
And now I feel like from this point on,
all bets are off.

1433
01:16:47,561 --> 01:16:48,604
Mm.

1434
01:16:48,687 --> 01:16:51,148
There's no telling what will happen
between her and Su-been.

1435
01:16:51,231 --> 01:16:52,441
Ah.

1436
01:16:54,109 --> 01:16:57,279
PARADISE
KIM MIN-GEE & LIM SU-BEEN

1437
01:16:57,362 --> 01:16:59,114
Hey, you know what's really weird?

1438
01:16:59,197 --> 01:17:02,284
I thought if I'm with you,
like, if I came here with you,

1439
01:17:02,367 --> 01:17:05,787
I'd be wondering about what's going on
with the people in Inferno,

1440
01:17:05,871 --> 01:17:06,913
but I'm not.

1441
01:17:08,832 --> 01:17:10,083
Hmm.

1442
01:17:10,167 --> 01:17:13,337
I'm the same.
Maybe it's because I'm just focused.

1443
01:17:13,420 --> 01:17:15,589
You're not thinking about Hee-sun?

1444
01:17:15,672 --> 01:17:17,132
- Of course I am.
- You are?

1445
01:17:17,215 --> 01:17:18,800
I think about her every day.

1446
01:17:18,884 --> 01:17:21,219
So, how much do you like her?

1447
01:17:23,764 --> 01:17:25,390
I'm not thinking about Seung-il.

1448
01:17:25,474 --> 01:17:26,892
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1449
01:17:28,894 --> 01:17:30,812
- I'll see tomorrow.
- Hmm.

1450
01:17:30,896 --> 01:17:34,149
It's because I didn't see him
when I was alone in Inferno.

1451
01:17:34,232 --> 01:17:38,362
It was out of sight, out of mind.
And I honestly had a really great time.

1452
01:17:38,445 --> 01:17:42,240
- Mm.
- That's probably why this feels like that.

1453
01:17:42,324 --> 01:17:44,701
In my case, I was here
with her just yesterday.

1454
01:17:44,785 --> 01:17:45,786
Yeah, I guess.

1455
01:17:48,789 --> 01:17:52,376
I was really surprised
at how much fun I had with Su-been.

1456
01:17:52,459 --> 01:17:54,544
I don't think I really expected that.

1457
01:17:55,712 --> 01:17:59,257
I think that our dating styles,
our way of thinking

1458
01:17:59,341 --> 01:18:03,637
and our romantic sensibilities
just work really well together.

1459
01:18:03,720 --> 01:18:05,138
We were really compatible.

1460
01:18:06,181 --> 01:18:08,100
Let's not get too logical about it.

1461
01:18:08,183 --> 01:18:10,686
We don't want to be
calculating all the time

1462
01:18:10,769 --> 01:18:12,479
when it comes
to a boyfriend or girlfriend.

1463
01:18:12,562 --> 01:18:15,190
That's what we said to each other
when we talked, remember?

1464
01:18:15,273 --> 01:18:18,568
If you're busy liking each other,
how do you have time for calculating?

1465
01:18:18,652 --> 01:18:19,569
Yeah.

1466
01:18:20,779 --> 01:18:21,863
How interesting.

1467
01:18:21,947 --> 01:18:23,448
It was really fun.

1468
01:18:23,532 --> 01:18:26,868
I'm even more intrigued now
than I thought I would be, honestly.

1469
01:18:28,412 --> 01:18:30,706
- Really?
- This is not good.

1470
01:18:30,789 --> 01:18:32,082
Oh, boy.

1471
01:18:32,582 --> 01:18:34,584
I actually used to be an athlete.

1472
01:18:37,587 --> 01:18:38,505
I played baseball.

1473
01:18:38,588 --> 01:18:40,799
- Really?
- Yeah. I played for ten years.

1474
01:18:40,882 --> 01:18:42,509
- Baseball?
- Yeah.

1475
01:18:45,345 --> 01:18:47,347
- Is that really so shocking?
- Yeah.

1476
01:18:47,431 --> 01:18:50,225
It was my first time meeting
someone who matched me

1477
01:18:50,308 --> 01:18:54,396
in every single way from A to Z,
so I was really surprised.

1478
01:18:54,479 --> 01:18:56,982
- I do track.
- Mm.

1479
01:18:57,065 --> 01:18:58,150
That's so impressive.

1480
01:18:58,233 --> 01:19:00,902
Track is also a sport
where you continue to test your limits.

1481
01:19:00,986 --> 01:19:04,573
- Yeah. Every day is an internal battle.
- Exactly.

1482
01:19:04,656 --> 01:19:07,784
When I was an athlete,
I always competed against myself.

1483
01:19:07,868 --> 01:19:11,204
It wasn't about beating anyone else,
it was always about improving.

1484
01:19:11,288 --> 01:19:12,247
Yeah.

1485
01:19:12,330 --> 01:19:15,709
All I could think of
while we were there was,

1486
01:19:15,792 --> 01:19:20,046
"Ah, so there is actually someone
who is great inside and out."

1487
01:19:20,130 --> 01:19:22,174
How can someone be so similar to me?

1488
01:19:22,257 --> 01:19:24,342
- They really are similar.
- Mm.

1489
01:19:24,426 --> 01:19:26,762
Because he also used to be an athlete.

1490
01:19:30,223 --> 01:19:33,018
Man, we're similar.

1491
01:19:33,101 --> 01:19:35,145
Oh, yeah, this is bad.

1492
01:19:40,233 --> 01:19:42,861
- She's laughing flirtatiously.
- Yeah.

1493
01:19:42,944 --> 01:19:44,112
Min-gee's totally--

1494
01:19:44,196 --> 01:19:47,324
- Her laugh is different.
- She's being flirty today.

1495
01:19:47,407 --> 01:19:49,910
She is. She's really into him.
You can clearly tell.

1496
01:19:49,993 --> 01:19:52,037
This is the first time
she's talking to another guy.

1497
01:19:52,120 --> 01:19:53,830
Min-gee's turning on her charm.

1498
01:19:55,332 --> 01:19:58,418
- This is nice. I don't want to go back.
- Yeah.

1499
01:20:01,963 --> 01:20:04,966
- Oh, I have a question for you.
- Okay, ask away.

1500
01:20:05,050 --> 01:20:07,469
Right now may not be
the right time to ask you this,

1501
01:20:07,552 --> 01:20:09,513
- but I want to ask it anyway.
- Okay.

1502
01:20:10,680 --> 01:20:13,308
Has there been
a change in your preference?

1503
01:20:13,391 --> 01:20:14,976
- Change in preference?
- Yeah.

1504
01:20:15,060 --> 01:20:16,853
Has there been a change by any chance?

1505
01:20:18,563 --> 01:20:20,440
- From today?
- Yeah, from today.

1506
01:20:20,524 --> 01:20:21,483
From today.

1507
01:20:23,235 --> 01:20:25,278
"Have I made it onto the list?"

1508
01:20:25,362 --> 01:20:27,906
- Exactly. That's what she's asking.
- Mm.

1509
01:20:29,032 --> 01:20:30,909
I think Su-been's answer will be no.

1510
01:20:30,992 --> 01:20:32,994
- You think? I mean--
- Not yet?

1511
01:20:33,078 --> 01:20:33,995
No.

1512
01:20:37,290 --> 01:20:38,917
Uh…

1513
01:20:47,676 --> 01:20:50,178
I think I need to give it
some more thought. Yeah.

1514
01:20:50,262 --> 01:20:51,888
I don't think there's been a change yet,

1515
01:20:51,972 --> 01:20:54,516
but I did have a moment
of clarity about it.

1516
01:20:54,599 --> 01:20:56,017
Mm.

1517
01:20:56,852 --> 01:20:57,769
See?

1518
01:20:59,437 --> 01:21:01,606
- Nice and clear.
- No beating around the bush.

1519
01:21:01,690 --> 01:21:03,692
He doesn't say things he doesn't mean.

1520
01:21:04,359 --> 01:21:07,195
- What about you then, Min-gee?
- Hmm? Me?

1521
01:21:07,279 --> 01:21:08,738
- Mm.
- Me?

1522
01:21:08,822 --> 01:21:10,907
My heart belongs to Seung-il.

1523
01:21:10,991 --> 01:21:12,534
- Right.
- But…

1524
01:21:14,536 --> 01:21:18,248
- That's being seriously tested.
- Mm.

1525
01:21:18,331 --> 01:21:22,085
I'm really surprised, though,
because I didn't think we'd click so well

1526
01:21:22,168 --> 01:21:24,629
and have such identical values.

1527
01:21:24,713 --> 01:21:27,007
So right now, I'm a bit shook up

1528
01:21:27,090 --> 01:21:29,384
- because I'm suddenly uncertain.
- Mm.

1529
01:21:30,010 --> 01:21:34,764
I'm going to have to think some more
about what my true feelings are.

1530
01:21:35,348 --> 01:21:39,769
Because right now, I really like Seung-il,
but he's also caused me a lot of pain.

1531
01:21:39,853 --> 01:21:42,731
And that pain is the biggest
problem for me, I think.

1532
01:21:42,814 --> 01:21:43,773
Mm.

1533
01:21:43,857 --> 01:21:47,152
The thing is, you strike me
as a really sincere person.

1534
01:21:47,235 --> 01:21:48,778
I am always sincere.

1535
01:21:48,862 --> 01:21:53,575
So if in your current situation, you were
to change your mind just like that…

1536
01:21:53,658 --> 01:21:54,910
Mm.

1537
01:21:54,993 --> 01:21:58,330
…uh, it wouldn't feel sincere to me.

1538
01:21:59,039 --> 01:22:00,999
You know what I mean, right? It's like…

1539
01:22:01,750 --> 01:22:03,793
Right now, I'm having
a lot of fun with you.

1540
01:22:03,877 --> 01:22:05,086
- Me, too. Totally.
- Right?

1541
01:22:05,170 --> 01:22:07,672
I'm like, "That's right.
That's what he was like.

1542
01:22:07,756 --> 01:22:09,257
When I'm with him, he's like this."

1543
01:22:09,341 --> 01:22:12,302
I need to take the time to see
how I feel about these things on my own.

1544
01:22:12,385 --> 01:22:13,345
And you should, too.

1545
01:22:13,428 --> 01:22:14,429
- Mm.
- Yeah.

1546
01:22:15,472 --> 01:22:17,349
I think you're being tested, too.

1547
01:22:18,892 --> 01:22:21,811
Due to me.

1548
01:22:21,895 --> 01:22:23,688
Don't laugh. I'm embarrassed.

1549
01:22:23,772 --> 01:22:25,148
Don't laugh, damn it.

1550
01:22:26,024 --> 01:22:28,109
Oh, you're funny.

1551
01:22:28,193 --> 01:22:29,527
- I mean…
- Yeah.

1552
01:22:30,820 --> 01:22:34,491
I think Min-gee is actually
attracted to Su-been.

1553
01:22:34,574 --> 01:22:35,825
You can really tell here.

1554
01:22:35,909 --> 01:22:39,287
But don't you think
Su-been's not attracted to her?

1555
01:22:39,371 --> 01:22:42,499
I don't get the impression that Min-gee
is so attracted to Su-been

1556
01:22:42,582 --> 01:22:45,335
that her feelings for Seung-il
are truly being tested.

1557
01:22:45,418 --> 01:22:48,505
My read of the situation is that
she's still mad at Seung-il right now

1558
01:22:48,588 --> 01:22:49,464
and is hurt by him.

1559
01:22:49,547 --> 01:22:52,550
When she returns to Inferno,
it'll still be him in the end.

1560
01:22:52,634 --> 01:22:54,678
I don't think she's attracted
to the point that--

1561
01:22:54,761 --> 01:22:56,137
I think she's totally infatuated.

1562
01:22:56,221 --> 01:22:58,932
- I think--
- "You used to be an athlete?"

1563
01:22:59,015 --> 01:23:01,559
Right, so I think it's a 50-50 split.

1564
01:23:01,643 --> 01:23:03,979
She's attracted to him
and also feeling healed

1565
01:23:04,062 --> 01:23:06,731
by being with someone new
after going through so much.

1566
01:23:06,815 --> 01:23:08,358
It's a mixture of both.

1567
01:23:08,441 --> 01:23:11,945
PARADISE
LEE JOO-YOUNG & KIM JAE-JIN

1568
01:23:12,028 --> 01:23:14,531
Wow, it's the Han River!

1569
01:23:15,991 --> 01:23:18,159
Allow me to escort you.

1570
01:23:18,243 --> 01:23:20,704
I'll go down first.
Hold my hand as you walk down.

1571
01:23:20,787 --> 01:23:22,038
There you go.

1572
01:23:22,122 --> 01:23:23,039
That's it.

1573
01:23:35,385 --> 01:23:37,679
A cruise. Amazing. Oh, my gosh.

1574
01:23:42,726 --> 01:23:46,104
After seeing so much of the
sea in Inferno, the Han River.

1575
01:23:48,273 --> 01:23:50,692
- It's such a welcome change.
- I know.

1576
01:23:50,775 --> 01:23:52,027
Oh, we're moving.

1577
01:23:53,278 --> 01:23:55,030
- We're moving.
- Yeah, we are.

1578
01:23:56,239 --> 01:23:58,908
Oh, my goodness!

1579
01:23:58,992 --> 01:24:02,370
We're moving. A cruise just for us.

1580
01:24:02,454 --> 01:24:04,039
I can't believe this.

1581
01:24:04,122 --> 01:24:06,291
- They're alone?
- Really?

1582
01:24:06,374 --> 01:24:07,792
Wow.

1583
01:24:07,876 --> 01:24:10,462
That is so romantic, isn't it?

1584
01:24:10,545 --> 01:24:13,339
- Shall we take a picture here?
- Before we eat?

1585
01:24:13,423 --> 01:24:14,841
- Let's take one.
- Okay.

1586
01:24:18,261 --> 01:24:20,555
This view's beautiful.

1587
01:24:20,638 --> 01:24:23,683
- Wow, that's so pretty.
- Stand there.

1588
01:24:23,767 --> 01:24:26,478
- Wow. This is insane.
- You can look at the camera here.

1589
01:24:26,561 --> 01:24:28,605
Or just do a candid shot.

1590
01:24:28,688 --> 01:24:31,316
- Make sure I look good.
- That's nice.

1591
01:24:31,399 --> 01:24:34,110
Wow. This is all so stunning.

1592
01:24:34,194 --> 01:24:35,695
Wow.

1593
01:24:38,656 --> 01:24:40,075
- Turn around.
- Mm.

1594
01:24:42,202 --> 01:24:45,080
- Here we go. One, two, three.
- Okay.

1595
01:24:46,915 --> 01:24:49,918
One more photo. One, two, three.

1596
01:24:57,717 --> 01:24:59,803
I'll take one of you. I want to take one.

1597
01:24:59,886 --> 01:25:01,096
Okay?

1598
01:25:01,179 --> 01:25:03,431
- No, let's take a selfie.
- Why not?

1599
01:25:03,515 --> 01:25:05,100
- Are you feeling shy?
- Yes.

1600
01:25:05,183 --> 01:25:06,601
- Come on, let's take a selfie.
- No.

1601
01:25:06,684 --> 01:25:08,520
- Can we please?
- I'm going to take one of you.

1602
01:25:08,603 --> 01:25:11,940
Come on. The sun's setting.
Let's do it. Stand there.

1603
01:25:12,023 --> 01:25:14,484
Come on.

1604
01:25:16,861 --> 01:25:19,697
- One.
- Line the shot up like this.

1605
01:25:19,781 --> 01:25:21,658
Oh, oh. Stay exactly like that.

1606
01:25:22,951 --> 01:25:24,410
Lower your hands a bit.

1607
01:25:24,494 --> 01:25:25,995
Higher.

1608
01:25:26,079 --> 01:25:27,163
Lower.

1609
01:25:27,831 --> 01:25:29,666
Uh, more this way.

1610
01:25:33,920 --> 01:25:35,004
Whoo-hoo!

1611
01:25:35,088 --> 01:25:37,924
- You take direction well.
- Oh, this is tough.

1612
01:25:40,009 --> 01:25:42,262
A lot of guys are shy
about taking pictures.

1613
01:25:42,345 --> 01:25:43,471
They really are.

1614
01:25:43,555 --> 01:25:44,806
He's doing this for her.

1615
01:25:44,889 --> 01:25:48,935
- You're right. He's only doing it for her.
- I feel like I'm watching myself.

1616
01:25:51,980 --> 01:25:52,856
Hold on.

1617
01:25:53,898 --> 01:25:55,066
Okay.

1618
01:26:05,827 --> 01:26:07,495
Ooh, I love the vibe.

1619
01:26:07,579 --> 01:26:09,455
I like these. You look good in them.

1620
01:26:12,959 --> 01:26:14,586
This is so nice.

1621
01:26:20,717 --> 01:26:22,510
- Thanks to you.
- This is so healing.

1622
01:26:22,594 --> 01:26:25,847
Thanks for getting you out of Inferno
and taking you to Hawaii?

1623
01:26:28,933 --> 01:26:31,019
Let's just tell everyone
that we went to Hawaii.

1624
01:26:31,102 --> 01:26:33,855
- This is Hawaii.
- Tell them we went somewhere like that.

1625
01:26:41,863 --> 01:26:43,198
So nice.

1626
01:26:43,281 --> 01:26:45,783
- That's beautiful.
- They're beautiful together.

1627
01:26:45,867 --> 01:26:48,203
They really look
so good together like that.

1628
01:26:48,286 --> 01:26:51,414
- Joo-young is bubbly, and Jae-jin is calm.
- Mm.

1629
01:26:53,750 --> 01:26:56,628
- I want to cut it for you.
- You don't mind?

1630
01:26:58,338 --> 01:26:59,339
What can I do?

1631
01:26:59,422 --> 01:27:02,133
Keep talking as I do this.

1632
01:27:06,095 --> 01:27:07,513
I'll cut yours for you then.

1633
01:27:09,307 --> 01:27:10,892
I'll try and tailor it to you.

1634
01:27:18,107 --> 01:27:19,025
Wow.

1635
01:27:21,152 --> 01:27:22,612
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1636
01:27:23,154 --> 01:27:25,782
Cutting up steak for each other.

1637
01:27:25,865 --> 01:27:28,785
- How did I do?
- Oh, this is great. It's perfect.

1638
01:27:28,868 --> 01:27:30,411
I tried my best to tailor it to you.

1639
01:27:31,788 --> 01:27:34,666
- The perfect size for you.
- Is it normal to be this happy?

1640
01:27:37,335 --> 01:27:38,294
Cheers.

1641
01:27:46,678 --> 01:27:49,889
I feel like
when we're in Inferno together,

1642
01:27:49,973 --> 01:27:53,601
there are so many situations
that naturally bring us together to talk.

1643
01:27:54,477 --> 01:27:55,770
Is that just me?

1644
01:27:56,354 --> 01:27:59,148
- That was by my design.
- Oh, it was, was it?

1645
01:27:59,232 --> 01:28:02,151
- Like you stayed behind on purpose?
- Yeah.

1646
01:28:02,235 --> 01:28:03,695
- Today, too?
- Yeah.

1647
01:28:05,363 --> 01:28:07,365
EARLIER TODAY DURING LUNCH

1648
01:28:13,496 --> 01:28:15,748
- I'm so bored.
- Yeah? You bored?

1649
01:28:15,832 --> 01:28:17,917
Oh, shall we clean up?

1650
01:28:26,050 --> 01:28:28,720
- Did you have half of that?
- This?

1651
01:28:28,803 --> 01:28:29,679
- Yeah.
- I did.

1652
01:28:29,762 --> 01:28:31,431
- How many did you have?
- Sweet potato.

1653
01:28:31,514 --> 01:28:32,557
Yeah.

1654
01:28:32,640 --> 01:28:34,100
Did you have a lot?

1655
01:28:35,560 --> 01:28:36,728
- Were you hungry?
- Huh?

1656
01:28:36,811 --> 01:28:37,979
- Were you hungry?
- No.

1657
01:28:38,479 --> 01:28:41,482
You didn't get up
because everyone else did, right?

1658
01:28:41,566 --> 01:28:43,359
Mm. No.

1659
01:28:43,443 --> 01:28:45,528
I won the game
because I ate a lot yesterday.

1660
01:28:45,611 --> 01:28:48,156
- Oh, did you really?
- Yeah, I really did.

1661
01:28:48,239 --> 01:28:50,950
- I heard a rumor, you had lamb chops.
- Yeah, it's true.

1662
01:28:52,827 --> 01:28:55,705
But for me, it's the way
you maneuver the situation

1663
01:28:55,788 --> 01:28:58,875
so you can approach me in a natural way.

1664
01:28:58,958 --> 01:29:00,543
It shows me that you're considerate.

1665
01:29:00,626 --> 01:29:04,255
The sense I got was that you hung
around deliberately because you knew.

1666
01:29:04,756 --> 01:29:07,342
- You knew I was staying behind.
- You're right.

1667
01:29:07,425 --> 01:29:10,219
We both picked up
on what the other was doing.

1668
01:29:10,303 --> 01:29:13,389
It felt natural because we understood
each other's intentions.

1669
01:29:14,057 --> 01:29:16,768
That's why I really like
what we have between us.

1670
01:29:16,851 --> 01:29:18,561
It's not forced at all.

1671
01:29:24,025 --> 01:29:25,651
I really don't know what to say.

1672
01:29:30,239 --> 01:29:31,074
Ah.

1673
01:29:37,997 --> 01:29:39,499
You're a really good person.

1674
01:29:41,125 --> 01:29:42,085
I am?

1675
01:29:44,712 --> 01:29:47,215
I really appreciate you saying that to me.

1676
01:29:50,009 --> 01:29:52,053
I'm truly not worthy of you.

1677
01:29:54,389 --> 01:29:57,308
You should never have to experience
any pain because of me.

1678
01:29:59,435 --> 01:30:01,562
I don't think you've done
something like that before.

1679
01:30:01,646 --> 01:30:03,523
- Right.
- Mm.

1680
01:30:04,107 --> 01:30:07,610
Really, I can tell that
you haven't because…

1681
01:30:08,986 --> 01:30:11,447
you express your feelings for me so well

1682
01:30:11,531 --> 01:30:14,075
that I can pick up
on everything right away.

1683
01:30:15,868 --> 01:30:18,538
- So I've never been--
- I think I'm gonna cry.

1684
01:30:18,621 --> 01:30:21,332
I've never been confused
about your feelings.

1685
01:30:22,375 --> 01:30:26,212
I hope you're not confused either.
That's why I wanted to come here with you.

1686
01:30:26,295 --> 01:30:28,464
The only reason I tried so hard
in the game today

1687
01:30:28,548 --> 01:30:31,717
was because I wanted to come here
with you and only you.

1688
01:30:32,927 --> 01:30:33,845
Thank you.

1689
01:30:35,263 --> 01:30:36,556
- Truly.
- Mm.

1690
01:30:37,348 --> 01:30:40,601
To me, the way things felt
so natural between us, even here,

1691
01:30:42,270 --> 01:30:44,105
is something that truly can't be compared

1692
01:30:44,188 --> 01:30:46,441
to anything I have ever had or experienced

1693
01:30:46,524 --> 01:30:50,111
with anyone else before. Yeah.

1694
01:30:50,194 --> 01:30:54,282
This is so precious to me, really.
If I had to describe it, it's precious.

1695
01:31:06,169 --> 01:31:07,962
Oh, look, the fountain!

1696
01:31:09,213 --> 01:31:11,007
That's so pretty.

1697
01:31:11,090 --> 01:31:13,301
Oh, my goodness. It's like a movie.

1698
01:31:21,517 --> 01:31:24,770
Today is the best day
I've had in this past year.

1699
01:31:24,854 --> 01:31:27,440
Really? That means a lot.

1700
01:31:27,523 --> 01:31:30,943
- Wow.
- All of them are so open this season.

1701
01:31:31,027 --> 01:31:32,737
- These two are, right?
- Mm.

1702
01:31:32,820 --> 01:31:36,115
Jae-jin just said that today is
the best day he's had this past year.

1703
01:31:36,199 --> 01:31:38,701
Didn't Jae-jin literally look
like he was choking up?

1704
01:31:38,784 --> 01:31:40,286
- Totally.
- He looked really touched.

1705
01:31:40,369 --> 01:31:43,331
Don't forget that he's a poet,
so he must feel all the emotions

1706
01:31:43,414 --> 01:31:45,583
being conveyed to him in their entirety.

1707
01:31:45,666 --> 01:31:47,001
That's the life of an empath.

1708
01:31:47,084 --> 01:31:48,920
And did you hear him earlier when he said

1709
01:31:49,003 --> 01:31:52,006
"You should never have to experience
any hurt because of me."

1710
01:31:52,089 --> 01:31:54,509
I feel the way Jae-jin--
How should I put it?

1711
01:31:54,592 --> 01:31:57,929
The way he took his time,
rather than rushing things, has paid off.

1712
01:31:58,012 --> 01:31:59,847
That's exactly right.

1713
01:31:59,931 --> 01:32:02,767
Joo-young has come to a realization
and made up her mind.

1714
01:32:02,850 --> 01:32:06,229
Because I don't think I've ever
seen her express herself this way.

1715
01:32:06,312 --> 01:32:08,773
This date was the moment
Joo-young gained clarity

1716
01:32:08,856 --> 01:32:11,275
and realized
who she feels the happiest with,

1717
01:32:11,359 --> 01:32:13,444
who she feels the most comfortable with,

1718
01:32:13,528 --> 01:32:16,489
and, most importantly,
who makes her feel the most loved.

1719
01:32:17,365 --> 01:32:18,533
INFERNO

1720
01:32:18,616 --> 01:32:20,535
Go-eun, where do you want to talk?

1721
01:32:20,618 --> 01:32:22,578
I thought this place looked nice.

1722
01:32:22,662 --> 01:32:24,747
- Shall we go there?
- Yeah.

1723
01:32:24,830 --> 01:32:25,873
Let's go up.

1724
01:32:27,083 --> 01:32:29,043
I've never been up here before.

1725
01:32:29,835 --> 01:32:31,462
- For your lap.
- Thanks.

1726
01:32:31,546 --> 01:32:33,005
- You're welcome.
- Aren't you cold?

1727
01:32:33,089 --> 01:32:35,758
No. The weather is beautiful right now.

1728
01:32:35,841 --> 01:32:37,802
That's so pretty.

1729
01:32:40,763 --> 01:32:42,640
Did you have a good chat?

1730
01:32:42,723 --> 01:32:45,101
What did you talk about?
I'm really curious, actually.

1731
01:32:45,184 --> 01:32:49,522
With I-geon, I always have these
really deep conversations.

1732
01:32:49,605 --> 01:32:50,523
Mm.

1733
01:32:50,606 --> 01:32:54,193
Like, serious conversations
about who I truly am deep down.

1734
01:32:54,277 --> 01:32:57,405
- That's a good thing, right?
- Yeah. I enjoy talking with him.

1735
01:32:57,488 --> 01:32:58,948
What did you talk about?

1736
01:32:59,448 --> 01:33:00,616
You know, just…

1737
01:33:01,742 --> 01:33:04,620
- This and that?
- Yeah, just this and that.

1738
01:33:05,413 --> 01:33:06,998
So I really…

1739
01:33:07,081 --> 01:33:12,086
Well, last night, I-geon also told me
that you had deep convos out of the blue.

1740
01:33:12,169 --> 01:33:13,170
Mm.

1741
01:33:13,963 --> 01:33:17,550
- Yeah, he just told me point-blank.
- Mm-hmm.

1742
01:33:17,633 --> 01:33:20,761
I guess it sounds like talking with Ha-eun
is really what made him--

1743
01:33:20,845 --> 01:33:24,348
Positive? Yeah, it definitely
made him make up his mind, so…

1744
01:33:25,182 --> 01:33:26,058
Hmm.

1745
01:33:27,727 --> 01:33:30,104
Oh. Mm.

1746
01:33:30,187 --> 01:33:33,441
I've been thinking
you must just have a charm about you.

1747
01:33:33,524 --> 01:33:35,735
- You must be irresistible.
- Me?

1748
01:33:37,153 --> 01:33:40,656
I did enjoy our conversation,
but am I attracted to him?

1749
01:33:40,740 --> 01:33:41,699
What--

1750
01:33:41,782 --> 01:33:45,036
What is it about me
that you find the most attractive?

1751
01:33:45,786 --> 01:33:48,372
Maybe it's because you're
the first guy I went to Paradise with.

1752
01:33:48,456 --> 01:33:49,457
Mm.

1753
01:33:50,082 --> 01:33:53,919
- I mean, that could have definitely--
- That was significant for me. Yeah.

1754
01:33:54,003 --> 01:33:55,796
That could have been a factor.

1755
01:33:56,964 --> 01:33:59,050
- A big factor.
- Because we really talked a lot.

1756
01:33:59,133 --> 01:34:02,678
And then for the next few days,
you were the guy I talked to the most.

1757
01:34:02,762 --> 01:34:03,929
Mm.

1758
01:34:04,013 --> 01:34:06,265
So there really wasn't anything
that led to me

1759
01:34:06,349 --> 01:34:08,309
being attracted to other people here.

1760
01:34:08,392 --> 01:34:12,229
But there are guys you were curious about.
It's the same for me.

1761
01:34:12,313 --> 01:34:13,773
That's just the way it is here.

1762
01:34:13,856 --> 01:34:15,941
With you, though, I think you and I

1763
01:34:16,025 --> 01:34:19,570
became attracted to each other
at a really similar pace, you know.

1764
01:34:19,654 --> 01:34:22,198
Like, not too fast, not too slow, just--

1765
01:34:22,281 --> 01:34:25,201
Yeah. And we both kind of… I don't know.

1766
01:34:26,369 --> 01:34:29,455
- That's how it felt to me anyway.
- That it was a good pace?

1767
01:34:29,538 --> 01:34:30,956
Mm.

1768
01:34:33,793 --> 01:34:36,379
It seems like Go-eun is only
interested in Sung-min after all.

1769
01:34:36,462 --> 01:34:39,965
I understand that. But to me, I feel
like she's more attracted to I-geon.

1770
01:34:40,049 --> 01:34:41,342
That's the way she comes across.

1771
01:34:41,425 --> 01:34:43,594
But for some reason
she keeps saying it's Sung-min.

1772
01:34:43,678 --> 01:34:47,139
When she chats with I-geon,
she talks more about herself

1773
01:34:47,223 --> 01:34:48,849
and they have deeper conversations.

1774
01:34:48,933 --> 01:34:51,644
But with Sung-min,
they just talk about vague stuff.

1775
01:34:51,727 --> 01:34:54,146
- They're shallow conversations.
- With no substance.

1776
01:34:54,230 --> 01:34:56,524
Exactly.
Conversations with no point to them.

1777
01:34:56,607 --> 01:34:59,652
Things like "We went at the same pace.
Not too slow, not too fast."

1778
01:34:59,735 --> 01:35:01,195
Like…

1779
01:35:01,278 --> 01:35:03,656
No, seriously. You know what I mean?

1780
01:35:03,739 --> 01:35:06,951
It requires some type of response,
but there's nothing behind it.

1781
01:35:07,034 --> 01:35:09,412
It's like he's just responding
for the sake of responding.

1782
01:35:09,495 --> 01:35:10,913
- Don't you think?
- Exactly.

1783
01:35:10,996 --> 01:35:13,457
That's why we can't detect
any chemistry between.

1784
01:35:13,541 --> 01:35:15,418
But from her perspective, she may prefer

1785
01:35:15,501 --> 01:35:18,379
that kind of conversation
to something too deep.

1786
01:35:18,462 --> 01:35:21,841
There may be attraction, but she may
feel more comfortable with Sung-min.

1787
01:35:21,924 --> 01:35:25,720
It could be something like that,
but I truly don't know.

1788
01:35:25,803 --> 01:35:30,224
But actually, when I-geon's with Go-eun,
it's not like he's trying to force

1789
01:35:30,307 --> 01:35:32,393
all this deep, heavy stuff out of her.

1790
01:35:32,476 --> 01:35:34,895
- He doesn't do that.
- She feels comfortable

1791
01:35:34,979 --> 01:35:37,481
and comes out with it totally unprompted.

1792
01:35:38,315 --> 01:35:40,443
It's I-geon, whichever way you look at it.

1793
01:35:42,778 --> 01:35:44,905
Where are you both going?

1794
01:35:44,989 --> 01:35:46,949
We're just wandering aimlessly.

1795
01:35:47,533 --> 01:35:48,826
I'm looking for Go-eun.

1796
01:35:51,412 --> 01:35:54,039
Here he is. The beast is on his way.

1797
01:35:54,123 --> 01:35:56,751
Right.

1798
01:35:57,793 --> 01:36:00,045
Oh, there she is.

1799
01:36:00,129 --> 01:36:01,046
There's my love.

1800
01:36:02,339 --> 01:36:04,049
"My love."

1801
01:36:05,301 --> 01:36:06,218
Go-eun!

1802
01:36:09,138 --> 01:36:10,848
Oh. Yeah?

1803
01:36:12,975 --> 01:36:15,436
When are you gonna hang out with me?
